# Incremental changes from v2 → v3 (add/subtract fastpath + accumulator)
#
# These changes are applied ON TOP of the v2 patch.
# Total new lines: ~60 in BigDecimal.java + 1 new file (FastDecimalAccumulator.java)
#
# Change 1: Public add(BigDecimal) — inline same-scale fastpath
#   Before: add(augend) → add(long,int,long,int) → add(long,long,int) → add(long,long) → valueOf
#   After:  add(augend) → inline overflow check → valueOf (3 fewer dispatches)
#
# Change 2: Public subtract(BigDecimal) — inline same-scale direct subtraction
#   Before: subtract(subtrahend) → add(xs, s1, -ys, s2) → negation + recursive add chain
#   After:  subtract(subtrahend) → inline subtraction overflow check → valueOf
#   (Note: direct subtraction avoids Long.MIN_VALUE negation edge case)
#
# Change 3: Private add(long,int,long,int) — eliminate recursive calls
#   Before: scale alignment → recursive add(scaledX, ys, scale2) → add(xs, ys, scale) → add(xs, ys) → valueOf
#   After:  scale alignment → inline overflow check → valueOf (2 fewer dispatches per call)
#
# New file: FastDecimalAccumulator — mutable accumulator
#   Eliminates intermediate object allocation entirely for accumulation patterns.
#   Performance: 3-11x faster than BigDecimal.add() chain for 100-1000 values.
